<div class="section">
    <h2>Core Philosophy: Why One Expensive Motor When 100 Cheap Ones Do More?</h2>
    <p>Original Chief Knock-A-Homer: one heavy spinner motor ‚Üí slow, expensive, easy to break.<br>Upgraded version: swarm of 100+ cheap brushless drone/ebike motors from Ali ‚Üí insane spin-up speed, lower weight, redundant (if 20 die, 80 still smash), and total BOM under $800.</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
    <h2>Key Upgrades ‚Äì Japan Tournament Ready</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Weapon:</strong> Horizontal spinner blade with 120 small hub motors (drone racing style) mounted in parallel ‚Üí 15,000+ RPM in 0.8 seconds.</li>
        <li><strong>Drive:</strong> 4WD with 40 ebike hub motors (500W each clone) ‚Üí instant torque, zero gear loss.</li>
        <li><strong>Armor:</strong> 3D-printed titanium-filled PLA panels + AR500 steel replaceable plates (cheap from Ali).</li>
        <li><strong>Battery:</strong> Sodium-ion packs recycled + cheap 18650 banks ‚Üí 5-minute fights no problem.</li>
        <li><strong>Brain:</strong> ESP32 swarm (20 units) + Arduino Mega clone for redundancy ‚Äì if one dies, others take over.</li>
        <li><strong>Troll Feature:</strong> Built-in speaker that plays Homer's "D'oh!" on hit + Flaming Moe fire effect (safe vape smoke + LED).</li>
    </ul>
</div>

